Lesson 1 Takeaways

1) Why databases?
	
	- Gives persistence and data structures for storing and searching data usually much it faster and easier than if we were to search a flat file
	- Ability to modify files at the same time

2) Why relational databases?

	- Offers tools for searching and querying data, and setting up constraints

3) How data bases happen:

	- Can call over a network
	- Can call over a library that keeps a database over a local disk